Performing the Reset Sequence through
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
METHOD 1
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	Through TCL Script

		1.Update the "path_to_folder" variable in vio_reset_seq.sh and in vio_reset_seq.tcl with the appropriate directory path for your system.After making the necessary changes, execute the script using:
./vio_reset_seq.sh

Note : In vio_reset_seq.tcl change path to .bit & .ltx files if necessary
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
METHOD 2
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	 Vivado Hardware Manager GUI

		1.Open Vivado -> Hardware Manager -> Open Target -> Auto Connect
		2.Program FPGA with:
			.bit file
			.ltx file
		3.Wait until DRAM calibration PASS (cal pass should become green)
		4.Open:
			hw_vio_1
			hw_vio_2
		5.In hw_vio_1:
			make sure rst_125mhz_int_uc = 1 otherwise follow  Reprogramming the Bitstream through Vivado GUI sequence
		6.In hw_vio_2: manually toggle
			RESET_TO_PROCESSOR (0 ->1 -> 0)
			RESET_TO_NIC       (0 ->1 -> 0)
		7.In hw_vio_1: release reset
			Set rst_125mhz_int_uc = 0

	 Reprogramming the Bitstream through Vivado GUI:

		Before reprogramming (dumping) the bitstream through the Vivado Hardware Manager GUI, ensure that the following signal is set to 1:
			rst_125mhz_int_uc = 1

		This step is important because the signal may remain at 0 after a previous programming cycle, which can affect proper reinitialization of the design. Setting the 				signal to 1 ensures that the FPGA enters a clean reset state before the new bitstream is programmed.


